spans.text: I left the Muses long ago , Deserted all the tuneful band To right the files
Dodsley's new Musaeum , Or in a letter fair and clean Committed to the Magazine
that in fine I quit all commerce with the Nine
the jarring powers , And every trade
, The plumed troops , and neighing steed
Which John was used with nicest art To comb , and teach the curls to part
the belle air and jaunty pride
belle The precincts of the gay ruelle
with tarnished lace , And hunger pittured in my face
in my sorrows have the grace To take some pity on my case
most punctual and observant , Your most obliged humble servant
